headline: Xsolla Advances Global Gaming Education and Innovation in Collaboration With HP
summary: LOS ANGELES, December 02, 2025--Xsolla, a leading global video game commerce company that helps developers launch, grow, and monetize their games, today announced a strategic relationship with HP to connect education, technology, and entrepreneurship across the global games industry.

headline: HP’s Cost-Cutting, AI Shift, and Dividend Plan Might Change the Case for Investing in HPQ
summary: On November 25, 2025, HP Inc. announced its latest quarterly results, launched a major cost-cutting and AI-focused restructuring plan involving up to 6,000 layoffs, and declared a US$0.30 per share quarterly dividend for January 2026. In the same week, HP also confirmed new earnings guidance for fiscal 2026 and completed a repurchase of 18.3 million shares, while entering a wide-reaching Wi-Fi 6 patent licensing agreement as a resolution to ongoing litigation.
